(33, 'Very confident that India will be leader of Global South, says Denmark envoy Freddy Svane', 'image1-1694057434554-56839819.webp', '[\"latest\",\"business\"]', 'very-confident-that-india-will-be-leader-of-global-south,-says-denmark-envoy-freddy-svane', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Exuding confidence in New Delhi as the \"leader of the Global South\", Denmark\'s Ambassador to India, Freddy Svane said that the world needs a country like India which believes in democracy and rule of law, as alternative to powers who \"debt-trap\" the poor countries.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Svane called India the \"leader of the Global South\" and affirmed confidence that New Delhi will build between the Global South and other countries in the West.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">He called the G20 Summit the biggest chance for India to set the direction for the future global world order.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Speaking to ANI, Svane said, \"India has spent a lot of resources in securing that this summit will be the biggest, the greenest and the most successful one ever in G20. And G20 is much more relevant than we might think because that will set the direction for how we cope with climate change, shortage of food and all these challenges that are putting the world in a big crisis\".</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In an apparent reference to China, the Denmark envoy stated that the world needs a country that believed in Democracy as an alternative to \"other powers who are debt-trapping poor countries\"</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\"My take is very clear. We need an alternative to other powers who are debt-trapping poor countries. We need a country that believes in democracy, in the rule of law and that\'s India, India is an alternative to a better future where we also work with countries in such a way that we\'re not being trappe&nbsp;..</span></p><p><br></p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(35, 'Tinsukia\'s Karabi Gogoi Selected to Represent India in India-Japan Teacher Exchange Program', 'image1-1694267769820-922923077.jpeg', '[\"latest\",\"news\"]', 'tinsukia\'s-karabi-gogoi-selected-to-represent-india-in-india-japan-teacher-exchange-program', '<p>In a moment of great pride and recognition, Ms. Karabi Gogoi, an esteemed educator from Tinsukia, Assam, has been selected to represent India in the prestigious India-Japan Teacher Exchange Program. This program, a testament to the importance of educational collaboration between nations, not only acknowledges the talent and dedication of Ms. Gogoi but also fosters cross-cultural understanding and enriches the teaching-learning experience on both sides.</p><h2>The India-Japan Teacher Exchange Program</h2><p>The India-Japan Teacher Exchange Program is a bilateral initiative that aims to strengthen educational ties between India and Japan. It provides a platform for educators from both countries to exchange knowledge, teaching methodologies, and cultural insights. This program, which has been in existence for several years, plays a pivotal role in nurturing global citizens and promoting a harmonious world.</p><h2>Karabi Gogoi: A Beacon of Excellence</h2><p>Ms. Karabi Gogoi, an accomplished educator with a wealth of teaching experience, has been chosen as India\'s representative in this esteemed exchange program. Hailing from Tinsukia, a picturesque town in Assam, Ms. Gogoi has dedicated her career to nurturing young minds and fostering a love for learning. Her selection underscores not only her outstanding teaching skills but also her commitment to educational development.</p><p>Ms. Gogoi\'s teaching philosophy revolves around creating an engaging and inclusive learning environment that encourages creativity, critical thinking, and holistic development. Her dedication to her students and her innovative teaching methods have garnered her recognition not only within her community but also on a national level.</p><h2>Cross-Cultural Learning</h2><p>The India-Japan Teacher Exchange Program offers an invaluable opportunity for educators like Ms. Gogoi to immerse themselves in a different educational and cultural milieu. By spending time teaching in Japanese schools, she will gain fresh perspectives on teaching methodologies, classroom management, and student engagement.</p><p>Simultaneously, her presence in Japanese classrooms will provide students there with a unique opportunity to learn about India, its rich cultural heritage, and its educational practices. This cross-cultural exchange is a bridge of understanding, fostering global citizens who appreciate the diversity and interconnectedness of the world.</p><h2>Enhancing Bilateral Relations</h2><p>Education is not just about imparting knowledge; it\'s also about building lasting relationships. Ms. Gogoi\'s participation in the India-Japan Teacher Exchange Program contributes significantly to the strengthening of bilateral ties between the two countries. As she engages with her Japanese counterparts and students, cultural bonds will be formed, fostering goodwill and collaboration that extend beyond the classroom.</p><p>Ms. Karabi Gogoi\'s selection to represent India in the India-Japan Teacher Exchange Program is a moment of pride for Tinsukia, Assam, and the entire nation. Her journey as an ambassador of Indian education to Japan is not just a personal achievement but also a symbol of the importance of educational collaboration on the global stage. As she embarks on this remarkable journey, she carries with her the hopes and aspirations of her students, her community, and the nation at large, reinforcing the belief that education is a powerful tool for building bridges and creating a better, more interconnected world.</p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(37, 'India Proudly Opens Its Arms to Welcome Eminent World Leaders for the Prestigious G20 Summit', 'image1-1694267908669-570312682.jpeg', '[\"latest\",\"business\",\"news\"]', 'india-proudly-opens-its-arms-to-welcome-eminent-world-leaders-for-the-prestigious-g20-summit', '<p>In a grand display of international diplomacy and cooperation, India is set to host the prestigious G20 Summit, welcoming eminent world leaders to its vibrant and diverse shores. This gathering of global leaders promises to be a monumental event, fostering dialogue, cooperation, and innovative solutions to address pressing global challenges. As the world grapples with various economic, environmental, and health crises, India\'s role as the host nation signifies its growing influence on the world stage and its commitment to addressing global issues.</p><h2>A Beacon of Global Unity</h2><p>The G20, short for the Group of Twenty, is an international forum that brings together leaders from the world\'s largest economies. Established in 1999, the G20 Summit provides a platform for these leaders to discuss and coordinate policies on critical issues, including the global economy, climate change, and sustainable development. The G20 represents a collective effort to promote economic stability and sustainable growth in an increasingly interconnected world.</p><h2>India\'s Selection as the Host</h2><p>India\'s selection as the host of the G20 Summit underscores its growing prominence in global affairs. With its rapidly expanding economy, burgeoning population, and rich cultural heritage, India is a fitting choice to host this esteemed event. Prime Minister Narendra Modi has played a crucial role in India\'s increasing influence on the world stage, championing issues such as climate change, renewable energy, and global health.</p><h2>India\'s Commitment to Address Global Challenges</h2><p>The G20 Summit provides an opportunity for India to showcase its commitment to addressing pressing global challenges. One of the central themes of the summit is sustainable development, a critical issue in a world facing climate change, environmental degradation, and resource scarcity. India\'s ambitious renewable energy goals, investment in clean technology, and efforts to combat pollution are all topics that will be at the forefront of discussions.</p><p>Furthermore, India\'s handling of the COVID-19 pandemic and its role in vaccine production and distribution will also be on the agenda. As the world continues to battle the pandemic, India\'s pharmaceutical industry and vaccine diplomacy have gained international recognition.</p><h2>Promoting Inclusive Growth</h2><p>India\'s choice as the host nation aligns with its vision of promoting inclusive growth and development. As one of the world\'s most diverse countries, India understands the importance of addressing social and economic disparities. The G20 Summit provides a platform to discuss policies and initiatives aimed at reducing inequality and ensuring that the benefits of economic growth reach all segments of society.</p><h2>Cultural Exchange and Diplomacy</h2><p>The G20 Summit is not just about policy discussions; it also serves as an opportunity for cultural exchange and diplomacy. India\'s rich cultural heritage, with its art, music, cuisine, and traditions, will be on full display for visiting dignitaries. Such exchanges foster a deeper understanding and appreciation of the host country\'s culture and heritage, strengthening diplomatic ties and friendships.</p><p>India\'s proud hosting of the G20 Summit is a testament to its growing influence and commitment to addressing global challenges. As world leaders gather in India\'s embrace, the world will be watching with anticipation, hoping for productive discussions and innovative solutions to the pressing issues facing our planet. The G20 Summit is not just a meeting of nations; it is a gathering of minds, ideas, and aspirations, all with the goal of building a more prosperous, sustainable, and inclusive world for generations to come. India\'s role as the host nation underscores its dedication to this noble endeavor.  </p><p><br></p><p><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/piyushgoyalofficial_peoples-g20-activity-7106193385908047873-mxAo?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_android\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>More Info</strong></a></p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
