(39, 'Ganesh Darshan', 'image1-1694498252554-232749211.jpeg', '[\"events\",\"latest\"]', 'ganesh-darshan', '<p>ğ— ğ—œğ—Ÿğ—§ğ—¢ğ—¡ ğ—ğ—˜ğ—¬ğ—¡ğ—˜ğ—¦ KA RAJA&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>To register your interest to attend the event, please confirm via <a href=\"https://forms.gle/AW2PqBbkxcsw6r6U7\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://forms.gle/AW2PqBbkxcsw6r6U7</a></p><p><br></p><p>All are Welcome ğŸ™ğŸ»</p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(40, 'Sindoor khela event', 'image1-1694498392689-54667959.jpeg', '[\"latest\",\"events\"]', 'sindoor-khela-event', '<p>Welcome to our first ever Sindoor khela event in central London Trafalgar Square&nbsp;in British history on 29 th October Diwali on the square representing State of Bengal this year from 1.30 pm onwards on North Terrace (meet up point)</p><p>We will create waves with our Laal paad look&nbsp;</p><p>Dance practises will start soon with very simple steps&nbsp;</p><p>Two songs&nbsp;</p><p>Dola re Dola&nbsp;</p><p>Choreography by Akansha Padma and Shreya they will conduct zoom classes&nbsp;</p><p>Elo elo Dugga elo&nbsp;this one is Durga Pujo song&nbsp;very peppy and we are going to use&nbsp;some props&nbsp;if possible&nbsp;</p><p>Like Conch kulo Dhunuchi if possible&nbsp;</p><p>Look at the video ( choreography by Sohini&nbsp;Sonela&nbsp;and Trained choreographer Noopur Dutta)</p><p>This choreography will have Durga Ma formation by one group by the central group&nbsp;our showcase dance to promote Cultural awareness</p><p>After this Photosession&nbsp;will engage professional photographer&nbsp;</p><p>Sindoor Khela from 2 pm onwards&nbsp;</p><p>Itâ€™s a ritual done on last day of Durga pujo by married ladies bidding Ma Durga goodbye from her â€œMaayka â€œ to her celestial abode&nbsp;</p><p>We will talk about it more and do video bytes that day to put like a programme for media&nbsp;</p><p>I will get Dibbas of Sindoor which has been purified by purohit in Durga pujo to be used in this day&nbsp;</p><p>Normally it is done in presence of Ma Durga but we will play the video of it to give u a flavour of Daakh playing and Ulu Ulu&nbsp;sound to give you a idea about this absolutely heavenly ritual&nbsp;we will just use couple of light strokes&nbsp;of sindoor on on face and on bangles&nbsp;and mukh Mishti offering sweets&nbsp;</p><p>Photosession again&nbsp;</p><p>3 pm disperse&nbsp;</p><p>Dress code&nbsp;</p><p>Laal Paad Saree&nbsp;</p><p>I have shared the link for the source from the weaver if you want lot of you have shown interest but u can wear your own but uniformity of look very important&nbsp;</p><p>My personal feeling is purchase one as a souvenir for such a fantastic event&nbsp;</p><p>Registration fee Â£5 again for various things but mainly photographer and other paraphernalia we need&nbsp;</p><p>I will contact a DJ to see if we can get a mobile music system&nbsp;</p><p>Lastly you must join the Fb event page for all information re future events interact and share pictures as all info gets lost on WA&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/292297219114961/?ref=share_group_link\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/groups/292297219114961/?ref=share_group_link</a></p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(41, 'Appleâ€™s first made-in-India iPhone 15 to sell globally on launch day', 'image1-1694578832951-788092978.jpg', '[\"technology\",\"latest\",\"news\",\"business\",\"events\"]', 'appleâ€™s-first-made-in-india-iphone-15-to-sell-globally-on-launch-day', '<p>In a historic development, Apple is set to introduce its latest iPhone models, the iPhone 15 and iPhone 15 Plus, as made-in-India devices available for global sale on their launch day. This move represents a significant shift for Apple and a noteworthy milestone for India\'s manufacturing capabilities. While Apple has previously produced iPhones in India, these earlier attempts were marred by production delays, unable to match the efficiency of their Chinese counterparts. However, this time around, Apple is gearing up to offer the iPhone 15 series right from the start.</p><p>The production of the iPhone 15 series in India commenced at the Foxconn factory in Sriperumbudur, Tamil Nadu, in early August. This development marks a critical step in Apple\'s broader strategy to diversify its supply chain away from China, particularly in light of disruptions caused by the global pandemic. Previously, the Cupertino giant primarily relied on China for iPhone manufacturing, but this shift to emerging markets like India has become increasingly vital.</p><p>To put this into perspective, the iPhone 15 is the first latest-generation Apple device produced in India and made available for sale on its launch day. It\'s worth noting that the earlier attempts took Apple several months to roll out Indian-produced units for sale. However, over the past year, they have made substantial progress, reducing the time to just a few weeks.</p><p>Nevertheless, while India is now playing a more significant role in Apple\'s manufacturing ecosystem, the company still relies on China for the assembly of its premium models, including the iPhone 15 Pro and iPhone 15 Pro Max.</p><p>Overall, this development signifies Apple\'s commitment to diversifying its manufacturing base and reducing its dependence on China. Currently, Apple\'s suppliers in India collectively produce about 7% of the total number of iPhones manufactured worldwide. This move has significant implications not only for Apple but also for India\'s growing role in global electronics manufacturing.</p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(47, 'India\'s Dominant Victory: A Resounding 10-Wicket Triumph', 'image1-1695047064747-748455440.jpeg', '[\"latest\"]', 'india\'s-dominant-victory:-a-resounding-10-wicket-triumph', '<p> </p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(48, 'Indian Medical Graduates Can Now Practise In US, Australia, Canada', 'image1-1695289194933-436330632.jpg', '[\"latest\",\"news\"]', 'indian-medical-graduates-can-now-practise-in-us,-australia,-canada', '<p>The Public Clinical Commission (NMC), India, has been being granted the sought after World Organization for Clinical Training (WFME) Acknowledgment Status for a residency of 10 years, as per an official statement from the Association Wellbeing Service.</p><p>WFME acknowledgment will empower Indian clinical alumni to seek after postgraduate preparation and practice in different nations that require WFME acknowledgment, like the US, Canada, Australia, and New Zealand, the delivery added.</p><p><br></p><p>Under this authorization every one of the 706 existing clinical schools become WFME licensed and the new clinical universities that will be set up in the approaching 10 years will naturally become WFME certify.</p><p><br></p><p>This will likewise make India an alluring objective for worldwide understudies because of our universally perceived norms.</p><p><br></p><p>Aside from this, the NMC will get the honor of upgrading the quality and principles of clinical training in India by adjusting them to the worldwide prescribed procedures and benchmarks.</p><p><br></p><p>The delivery added that acknowledgment will expand the global acknowledgment and notoriety of Indian clinical schools and experts, work with scholastic joint efforts and trades and advance nonstop improvement and development in clinical training and encourage a culture of value confirmation among clinical teachers and organizations.</p><p><br></p><p>The World League for Clinical Schooling (WFME) is a worldwide association devoted to improving the nature of clinical instruction around the world. WFME\'s main goal is to take a stab at better medical care for all humankind; WFME\'s essential goal is to improve the nature of clinical training around the world, with the advancement of the greatest logical and moral guidelines in clinical schooling, as per the Wellbeing Service public statement.</p><p><br></p><p>The delivery expressed that the Schooling Commission on Unfamiliar Clinical Training (ECFMG) is the essential body in the US that supervises the arrangements and guidelines around authorizing Global Clinical Alumni (IMGs). To take the USMLEs, and to apply for residency all IMGs should be ensured by ECFMG.</p><p><br></p><p>The Schooling Commission on Unfamiliar Clinical Training (ECFMG) is the essential body in the US that manages the approaches and guidelines around permitting Worldwide Clinical Alumni (IMGs).</p><p><br></p><p>To take the USMLEs, and to apply for residency all IMGs should be confirmed by ECFMG. This certificate ordinarily happens after the fulfillment of the second year of a clinical program, and prior to making the USMLE Stride 1 assessment.</p><p><br></p><p>In 2010, the ECFMG reported another necessity that will become successful in the year 2024 (was set for 2023 yet was moved to 2024 because of Coronavirus).</p><p><br></p><p>The new decide states that \"beginning in 2024, people applying for ECFMG Confirmation should be an understudy or graduate of a clinical school that is suitably certify. All the more explicitly, the school should be certify by an authorizing organization that is formally acknowledged by the World League for Clinical Training (WFME).\"</p><p><br></p><p>The WFME acknowledgment process involves a charge of â‚¹ 4,98,5142 ($60,000) per clinical school, which covers the costs of the site visit group and their movement and convenience.</p><p><br></p><p>This implies that the all out cost for the 706 clinical universities in India to apply for WFME acknowledgment would have been roughly â‚¹ 351.9 crore ($4,23,60,000). It is critical that NMC has taken acknowledgment of WFME which will be material to all clinical universities under its umbrella.</p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(54, 'Swaminarayan Akshardham in New Jersey: The Biggest Hindu Temple of the Modern Era in the USA', 'image1-1695729683709-113099568.png', '[\"news\",\"latest\",\"travel\"]', 'swaminarayan-akshardham-in-new-jersey:-the-biggest-hindu-temple-of-the-modern-era-in-the-usa', '<p>In the heart of New Jersey, a magnificent architectural wonder is set to be inaugurated â€“ the Swaminarayan Akshardham. This grand temple complex is not just a religious monument; it is a symbol of cultural richness and architectural excellence. As the largest Hindu temple of the modern era in the United States, it holds immense significance for the Indian diaspora and all those interested in exploring the cultural tapestry of Hinduism. In this blog, we will delve into the grandeur of the Swaminarayan Akshardham, its history, unique features, and its importance for the Hindu community in the USA.</p><h2>A Glimpse into the History</h2><p>The Swaminarayan Akshardham in New Jersey is part of the Swaminarayan Akshardham complex, a socio-spiritual cultural complex that has its roots in the Swaminarayan tradition of Hinduism. The Swaminarayan tradition, founded by Lord Swaminarayan in the early 19th century, emphasizes the worship of God in His divine form, Akshardham. It promotes spirituality, morality, and cultural preservation.</p><p>The Akshardham complex was conceived and developed by the Bochasanwasi Shri Akshar Purushottam Swaminarayan Sanstha (BAPS), an organization dedicated to preserving and promoting the cultural and spiritual heritage of India. The first Akshardham temple was built in Gandhinagar, India, and later, the concept was expanded to other major cities worldwide.</p><h2>Swaminarayan Akshardham in New Jersey: A Marvel of Architecture</h2><ol><li><span style=\"color: var(--tw-prose-bold);\">Architectural Marvel</span>: The Swaminarayan Akshardham in New Jersey is a masterpiece of architecture. Its intricately carved marble exteriors, stunning domes, and exquisite sculptures make it a visual treat. The temple\'s architecture blends traditional Indian design with modern technology, making it a harmonious amalgamation of the old and the new.</li><li><span style=\"color: var(--tw-prose-bold);\">Grandeur and Size</span>: What sets this temple apart is its sheer size. Covering an area of over 162 acres, it is the largest Hindu temple complex in the USA. The main temple stands 42 feet tall, while the central dome soars to a majestic height of 87 feet. The sprawling complex includes prayer halls, cultural exhibition spaces, and lush gardens.</li><li><span style=\"color: var(--tw-prose-bold);\">Cultural Exhibitions</span>: One of the most remarkable features of Swaminarayan Akshardham is its cultural exhibitions. Visitors can explore the rich history, philosophy, and contributions of Hinduism through state-of-the-art displays, dioramas, and multimedia presentations. These exhibitions are educational and provide an immersive experience for people of all backgrounds.</li><li><span style=\"color: var(--tw-prose-bold);\">Akshardham Mandir</span>: At the heart of the complex is the Akshardham Mandir, the main temple. Its sanctum sanctorum houses the sacred murti (idol) of Bhagwan Swaminarayan and His divine abode, Akshardham. Devotees and visitors can experience a sense of spirituality and tranquility within its walls.</li></ol><h2>Significance for the Hindu Community and Beyond</h2><p>The Swaminarayan Akshardham in New Jersey holds great significance for various communities:</p><ol><li><span style=\"color: var(--tw-prose-bold);\">Cultural Preservation</span>: It serves as a symbol of cultural preservation and propagation. The temple complex offers a platform for people to understand and appreciate the rich tapestry of Hindu culture, art, and spirituality.</li><li><span style=\"color: var(--tw-prose-bold);\">Religious and Spiritual Hub</span>: For the Hindu community in the USA, it provides a place of worship, reflection, and spiritual growth. It is a center for religious activities, festivals, and events.</li><li><span style=\"color: var(--tw-prose-bold);\">Educational Hub</span>: The cultural exhibitions at Swaminarayan Akshardham are educational not just for the Hindu community but for people of all backgrounds. They help bridge gaps in understanding and promote cultural harmony.</li><li><span style=\"color: var(--tw-prose-bold);\">Tourist Attraction</span>: Beyond its religious and cultural significance, Swaminarayan Akshardham is set to become a major tourist attraction, drawing visitors from across the country and the world. Its architectural beauty and educational value make it a must-visit destination.</li></ol><p>The Swaminarayan Akshardham in New Jersey is not just a temple; it\'s a cultural and architectural marvel that stands as a testament to the rich heritage of Hinduism. As the largest Hindu temple of the modern era in the USA, it opens doors for people of all backgrounds to explore, appreciate, and understand Hindu culture, spirituality, and history. Its inauguration is a momentous occasion that will undoubtedly leave a lasting impact on the landscape of religious and cultural diversity in the United States.</p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(56, 'Why everyone is bullish on India? A picture is worth a thousand words.', 'image1-1696506525041-315381672.jpeg', '[\"latest\",\"news\"]', 'why-everyone-is-bullish-on-india?-a-picture-is-worth-a-thousand-words.', '<p>Indian hashtag#economy accounts for 3% of the world in 2023. The GDP of India is $3.7 T out of the $105 T of the entire world. Although India is the 5th largest economy in the world, the difference between the Big 2 (USA and China) and the next 3 (Japan, Germany, and India) is massive.</p><p><br></p><p>The largest economies in the world â€“ The Big 2 &amp; everyone else</p><p><br></p><p>1. USA â€“ $26.9 T</p><p>2. China â€“ $19.4 T</p><p>3. Japan â€“ $4.4T</p><p>4. Germany â€“ $4.3T</p><p>5. hashtag#India â€“ $3.7T</p><p><br></p><p>The economic hashtag#growth is tepid in Japan and Germany because of the ageing population. The Japanese economy has hardly grown in the past 30 years. The German economic might is fading. India will overtake Japan and Germany and become the 3rd largest economy by 2027 with a $5T GDP. But that\'s just the start.</p><p><br></p><p>The gulf between India and China is immense. The Chinese economy is more than 5x that of India for a similar population size (1.4B people). China experienced phenomenal economic growth after joining the WTO in 2001. The developed world outsourced its manufacturing to China. It made China an economic superpower, second only to the USA.</p><p><br></p><p>But nothing lasts forever. Poor countries grow rich and vice versa. The economic cycle repeats. The Chinese sun is on the wane. As its population ages, its supercharged growth is coming to a screeching halt. Unlike the USA, China is not a destination for the smartest immigrants from other countries. It\'s on its own.</p><p><br></p><p>We often hear economists saying China will grow old before it becomes rich. It might be true.</p><p><br></p><p>This leaves India in an enviable position. While it might not achieve what China did (10% annual real growth for 30 years), a 6-8% real growth over the next 30 years is realistic.</p><p><br></p><p>It will reduce the gulf between India and the Big 2. Its share in the world GDP will increase from 3% to 10%.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>The world economy will roughly increase by $120 T ($223 T from $105 T) over the next 30 years. India will account for $18-19T of this increase.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>This represents immense opportunities to build wealth for the smartest investors. The world is long on India. So should be you :).</p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(57, 'UK\'s Superdry sells S. Asia licenses to India\'s Reliance Retail for $48 mln', 'image1-1696506831877-457145719.png', '[\"latest\",\"news\",\"business\"]', 'uk\'s-superdry-sells-s.-asia-licenses-to-india\'s-reliance-retail-for-$48-mln', '<p>BENGALURU, Oct 4 (Reuters) - Reliance Retail, India\'s largest retailer, will buy UK-based Superdry\'s licenses and brand assets in three Asian countries for 40 million pounds ($48 million), expanding its tie-ups with foreign brands and giving the struggling UK fashion retailer much-needed funds.</p><p>Superdry\'s shares&nbsp;<span style=\"color: inherit;\">(SDRY.L)</span>&nbsp;jumped 18% to a near two-month high on Wednesday after the company said it would use the expected 28.3 million pounds net proceeds to boost its liquidity and fund its capital needs as part of a turnaround plan.</p><p>The deal will be via a joint venture -- in which Superdry will invest 9.6 million pounds for a 24% stake -- and cover Sri Lanka, Bangladesh and India, where the UK company has been present since 2012 when it first partnered with Reliance Retail.</p><p>Billionaire Mukesh Ambani\'s Reliance Retail has more than 18,000 stores selling everything from groceries to electronics. It also has partnerships with foreign brands such as Jimmy Choo, Marks &amp; Spencer and Pret A Manger.</p><p>The company, which competes with Amazon&nbsp;<span style=\"color: inherit;\">(AMZN.O)</span>&nbsp;and Walmart\'s&nbsp;<span style=\"color: inherit;\">(WMT.N)</span>&nbsp;Flipkart, is in talks with investors including the sovereign wealth funds of Singapore, Abu Dhabi and Saudi Arabia for investments of around $1.5 billion, Reuters&nbsp;<span style=\"color: inherit;\">reported</span>&nbsp;last month.</p><p>On the other hand, Superdry, which mostly sells sweatshirts, hoodies and jackets, has been grappling with weak orders from wholesale partners as consumers deal with a cost-of-living crisis and fall in real wages.</p><p>Last month, it&nbsp;<span style=\"color: inherit;\">warned</span>&nbsp;of stunned revenue growth this year after posting a bigger-than-expected annual loss. It has been raising funds to bolster its finances and said cutting costs was a priority.</p><p>The deal with Reliance Retail, said Superdry, will help it \"focus on growing its brand and increasing sales in its more established territories, where it has strongest expertise.\"</p><p>The assets in the deal generated about 1.8% of total group sales in the financial year through April 30, said Superdry.</p><p>Shares of Reliance Industries&nbsp;<span style=\"color: inherit;\">(RELI.NS)</span>, the parent of Reliance Retail, were down 0.8% in afternoon trading. ($1 = 0.8286 pounds)</p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
(59, 'India Cricket Team for World Cup 2023 Players Name List', 'image1-1700143403411-896251864.jpg', '[\"latest\"]', 'india-cricket-team-for-world-cup-2023-players-name-list', '<p>The&nbsp;<strong>Indian National Cricket Team</strong>, commonly known as&nbsp;<strong>Team India</strong>, is overseen by the&nbsp;<strong>Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI)</strong>. They enjoy full membership in&nbsp;<strong>the International Cricket Council (ICC</strong>), which allows them to take part in&nbsp;<strong>Test Matches, One-Day Internationals (ODIs) and Twenty-20 Internationals (T20Is).</strong></p><p>Team India boasts intense rivalries with several other cricketing nations, with its most notable ones being against Pakistan. Additionally, competitive relationships are cultivated with teams like Australia, South Africa and England.</p><h2><strong>India National Cricket Team Players Name For World Cup 2023</strong></h2><p><strong>India squad for World Cup 2023</strong></p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Rohit Sharma (c),</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Hardik Pandya (vc),</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Shubman Gill,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Virat Kohli,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Shreyas Iyer,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">KL Rahul,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Ravindra Jadeja,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Shardul Thakur,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Jasprit Bumrah,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Mohammed Siraj,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Kuldeep Yadav,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Mohammed Shami,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Axar Patel,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Ishan Kishan,</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Suryakumar Yadav.</li></ul><h2>India National Cricket Team â€“ History</h2><p>The governing body of cricket in the country namely Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI).&nbsp;<strong>The first recorded match</strong>&nbsp;in India was in&nbsp;<strong>1721.</strong>&nbsp;The Indian Cricket team played its first official test match on&nbsp;<strong>25th&nbsp;June 1932</strong>&nbsp;at the famous&nbsp;<strong>Lordâ€™s cricket ground in England</strong>. Indian cricket played the test match with just six layers which make it traditionally strong at home but not really making an impact on away tours.</p><p>Indian Cricket team get stronger in the 1970s with the emergence of batsman:</p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Sunil Gavaskar</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Gundappa Viswanath</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">All-rounder Kapil Dev</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Quality spin bowlers</li></ul><p>India developed a more aggressive batting line-up with stroke makers such as&nbsp;<strong>Azharuddin, Dilip Vengsarkar and Ravi Shastri</strong>. In&nbsp;<strong>1983</strong>, India went to defeat the favorites and&nbsp;<strong>two-time defending</strong>&nbsp;<strong>champions West Indies in the third ICC Cricket World Cup</strong>. This created a point in Indian Sporting history.</p><p>The end of the 80s and 90s witnessed the debuts of&nbsp;<strong>Sachin Tendulkar, Saurav Ganguly, Rahul Dravid, Anil Kumble and Javagal Srinath,</strong>&nbsp;considered to be among the greatest Indian players and brought much glory for the country with their stellar contributions.</p><h2><strong>India National Cricket Team Captain</strong></h2><p><strong>Rohit Sharma</strong>&nbsp;is the captain of the Indian menâ€™s Cricket Team. He is popularly known as Hitman for his hard hitting skills,<strong>&nbsp;Rohit Sharma</strong>&nbsp;is a gifted batsman and an immensely talented cricketer who is pleasing on the eye with his elegance and ability to time the ball. Harmanpreet Kaur is the captain of the Indian womenâ€™s cricket team. She plays as an all rounder in the team and was&nbsp;&nbsp;was awarded the Arjuna Award for Cricket in the year 2017.</p><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><br></h2><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Captains:&nbsp;</strong>Rohit Sharma (Current Capt.), Virat Kohli (Previous captain) and MS Dhoni (Ex-Captain).</p><p><strong>Coaches:&nbsp;</strong>Rahul Dravid (head coach), Vikram Rathour (Batting Coach), Paras Mhambrey (bowling coach), T Dilip (fielding coach).</p><h2>Indian National Cricket Team Players Name For World Cup</h2><p>On&nbsp;<strong>23rd&nbsp;June 2023</strong>, the selection committee declared only test matches and ODI matches squad. For the Test and ODI series,&nbsp;<strong>Rohit Sharma will lead the team</strong>.&nbsp;<strong>On 5th&nbsp;July 2023</strong>, the&nbsp;<strong>BCCI&nbsp;</strong>declared the&nbsp;<strong>Indian Team Squad for T20s</strong>, where&nbsp;<strong>Hardik Pandya</strong>&nbsp;will lead the team.</p><p>Here is the India National Team Players 2023 list:</p><p><strong>S. No.PlayersAge</strong>1Rohit Sharma362Shubman Gill233Ruturaj Gaikwad264Virat Kohli345Surya Kumar Yadav326Sanju Samson287Ishan Kishan258Hardik Pandya299Shardul Thakur3110R Jadeja3411Axar Patel2912Yuzvendra Chahal3313Kuldeep Yadav2814Jaydev Unadkat3115Mohd. Siraj2916Urman Malik2317Mukesh Kumar29</p><h2>Indian National Cricket Team Ranking 2023</h2><p><strong>Position&nbsp;Test RankingODI RankingT20 Ranking1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>IndiaAustraliaIndia<strong>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>AustraliaPakistanEngland<strong>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>EnglandIndiaNew Zealand<strong>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>South AfricaNew ZealandPakistan<strong>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>New ZealandEnglandSouth Africa<strong>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>PakistanSouth AfricaAustralia<strong>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Sri LankaBangladeshWest Indies<strong>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>West IndiesAfghanistanSri Lanka<strong>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>BangladeshSri LankaBangladesh<strong>10.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>ZimbabweWest IndiesAfghanistan</p><h2><strong>India Team&nbsp;</strong>Governing Body</h2><p><strong>The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI)</strong>&nbsp;functions as the regulatory body for the Indian cricket team and first-class cricket in the country. Established in 1929, the Board represents India within the<strong>&nbsp;International Cricket Council (ICC)</strong>&nbsp;and operates from its headquarters located at the â€˜Cricket centreâ€™ in Churchgate, Mumbai, Maharashtra. Renowned for its significant financial standing, the BCCI is counted among the wealthiest sporting organizations globally. It garnered $612,000,000 by selling media rights for Indiaâ€™s matches from 2006 to 2010. Roger Binny currently serves as the BCCI president, and Jay Shah holds the position of secretary.</p><p>Indiaâ€™s upcoming matches are typically determined by the International Cricket Council through its future tours program. However, the BCCI, leveraging its substantial financial influence in the cricketing realm, has frequently contested the ICCâ€™s program. The Board has advocated for more series involving high-revenue teams like India, Australia, and England, contrasting with tours featuring teams such as Bangladesh or Zimbabwe. Instances of conflict between the BCCI and the ICC have also arisen in the past, particularly concerning sponsorships.</p><h2><strong>Indian&nbsp;</strong>Team Colours</h2><p>In Test cricket matches, the Indian team dons the traditional cricket whites, complemented by navy blue caps and helmets. In limited-overs matches, such as ODIs and T20s, the team sports uniforms with varying shades of blue. These outfits may also incorporate a splash of colors reflecting those present in the Indian national flag.</p><h2>Tournaments Wins by India National Cricket Team</h2><p><strong>World Cup:&nbsp;</strong>1983, 2011</p><p><strong>Champions Trophy:&nbsp;</strong>2002, 2013</p><p><strong>T20 World Cup:&nbsp;</strong>2007</p><p><strong>Asia Cup:&nbsp;</strong>1984, 1988, 1990-91, 1995, 2010, 2016 (T20), 2018.</p>', '2024-11-05 21:38:39'),
