(66, 'Usha Vance Becomes the Second Lady of the United States â€“ A Historic Milestone!', 'image1-1731911970347-402502664.png', '[\"news\"]', 'usha-vance-becomes-the-second-lady-of-the-united-states-a-historic-milestone', '<p>In an inspiring achievement, <strong>Usha Vance</strong> has made history by becoming the <strong>Second Lady of the United States</strong>. Her rise to this prominent position is a testament to her dedication, leadership, and groundbreaking journey in American politics.</p><p>What makes this accomplishment even more significant is that <strong>Usha is the first woman of Indian origin</strong> to achieve this remarkable feat, breaking new barriers for women and people of Indian descent in the global political landscape.</p><p>Her success serves as a powerful example of determination and the incredible impact Indian-origin individuals are making worldwide. ğŸ™Œ</p><p>For more inspiring success stories, visit <a href=\"http://www.globalindiansinfo.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">www.globalindiansinfo.com</a>.</p><p>ğŸ’¬ <strong>Join our WhatsApp group for more updates</strong>: <a href=\"https://chat.whatsapp.com/IBD5TnnlJA5JPNy3JSylxT\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://chat.whatsapp.com/IBD5TnnlJA5JPNy3JSylxT</a> </p><p>#InspiringSuccess #UshaVance #SecondLady #IndianOrigin #WomenInPolitics #Leadership #IndianAmericans #GlobalIndians #BreakingBarriers</p>', '2024-11-18 12:10:08'),
(67, 'US Visa Bulletin December 2024 Update', 'image1-1732013147750-954901343.png', '[\"news\",\"latest\"]', 'us-visa-bulletin-december-2024-update', '<p>The <strong>U.S. Department of State\'s December Visa Bulletin</strong> has been released, showing forward movement for Indian applicants in some Green Card categories, particularly in employment-based (EB) visa categories. This marks a positive shift for those awaiting their turn to secure a Green Card.</p><p>For <strong>EB applicants</strong>, the dates provided in the bulletin indicate the earliest time a visa can be issued or an adjustment of status application approved.</p><p>ğŸ”¹ <strong>Family-Sponsored Applications</strong>: The Visa Bulletin also outlines critical preference categories for family-sponsored immigrants:</p><ul><li><strong>First Preference (F1)</strong>: Unmarried Sons and Daughters of U.S. Citizens</li></ul><p>Stay updated on your Green Card process by visiting <a href=\"http://www.globalindiansinfo.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>www.globalindiansinfo.com</strong></a>.</p><p>ğŸ’¬ Join our <strong>WhatsApp group</strong> for more updates: <a href=\"https://chat.whatsapp.com/IBD5TnnlJA5JPNy3JSylxT\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://chat.whatsapp.com/IBD5TnnlJA5JPNy3JSylxT</a></p><p>#USVisaBulletin #GreenCard #IndianApplicants #EBCategories #FamilySponsored #VisaUpdate</p>', '2024-11-19 16:15:49'),
(68, 'PM Narendra Modi Honored with Guyana\'s Highest Civilian Award ', 'image1-1732530238844-414546740.png', '[\"latest\",\"news\",\"travel\"]', 'pm-narendra-modi-honored-with-guyanas-highest-civilian-award-', '<p>In a remarkable recognition of his leadership, India\'s Prime Minister Narendra Modi has been awarded Guyana\'s highest civilian honor, showcasing India\'s growing global influence and diplomatic ties.</p><p>This prestigious accolade reflects the strengthening of relationships between India and Guyana and highlights PM Modi\'s vision for a brighter, more interconnected world.</p><p>Stay updated on your <strong>Green Card process</strong> and other essential updates by visiting <a href=\"http://www.globalindiansinfo.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">www.globalindiansinfo.com</a>.</p><p>ğŸ’¬ <strong>Join our WhatsApp group</strong> for the latest updates and more: <a href=\"https://chat.whatsapp.com/IBD5TnnlJA5JPNy3JSylxT\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://chat.whatsapp.com/IBD5TnnlJA5JPNy3JSylxT</a></p><p><br></p>', '2024-11-25 15:54:04'),
(69, 'Historic Moment at Cambridge Union! ', 'image1-1733814954497-311954609.png', '[\"latest\",\"education\",\"news\"]', 'historic-moment-at-cambridge-union-', '<p>A British Indian student, <strong>Anoushka Kale</strong>, has been elected president of the <strong>University of Cambridge\'s historic Cambridge Union Society</strong>, one of the world\'s oldest debating societies, renowned as a defender of free speech since 1815.</p><p>Anoushka secured <strong>126 votes</strong> to be elected uncontested for the <strong>Easter 2025 term</strong> in a recent election. Currently serving as the Debates Officer, she aims to strengthen ties with cultural societies within the university, including the <strong>India Society</strong>.</p><p>ğŸ“š This milestone celebrates her efforts and showcases the vibrant contributions of the Indian diaspora.</p><p>Visit: <a href=\"http://www.globalindiansinfo.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">www.globalindiansinfo.com</a></p><p>ğŸ’¬ <strong>Join our WhatsApp group</strong> for the latest updates and more: <a href=\"https://chat.whatsapp.com/IBD5TnnlJA5JPNy3JSylxT\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://chat.whatsapp.com/IBD5TnnlJA5JPNy3JSylxT</a></p><p>Stay connected for more inspiring stories! ğŸŒâœ¨</p>', '2024-12-10 12:45:58');

